  Power Efficiency Benchmark
=================================================================
  x86  : 24 threads, 100.0W TDP, 4-cyc decode
  Bemi : 144 threads, 85.0W TDP, 4-cyc decode (x86 decoder KEPT)
  Note : IPC advantage from fusion only (1.3x). Bemi wins via thread density.
  Ops  : 1,000,000 high-level operations per category

   Category  x86 Time (rel)  Bemi Time (rel) Perf Gain  x86 Energy (J)  Bemi Energy (J) Efficiency Gain
 Arithmetic        208333.3          40064.1      5.2x        20833333          3405448           6.12x
String Copy        208333.3         213675.2     0.98x        20833333         18162393           1.15x

  Energy advantage sources:
    Arithmetic : 144 threads x 1.3 IPC -> 187.20000000000002 TP vs x86's 24.0 TP
    Despite 1.5x RISC expansion, 7.8x TP * (100/85 TDP ratio) -> compounding gain
    String Copy: 8x expansion but 7.8x TP -> still faster; 85W/100W seals the deal
